Subject: Dictated Sparse Realization Dense Node Framework Source

Description: Preserved source request to use periphery inspection to draw subjects into focus, delineate them, trace causal and casual relations, and let sparse realizations build into dense scoped nodes.

& [DictatedSparseRealizationDenseNodeFrameworkSource] is the preserved user direction
  + [source_status] is preserved_raw_direction
  + [captured_request] is start using the new periphery inspection system to draw things into focus, analyze and delineate, trace causal and casual relationships, and develop a .sop framework of sparse realizations that build into dense nodes as delineated subjects are clearly identified and scoped out and in
  + [active_project] is C:\Project\Pinky\RiemannHypothesis
  + [active_authority_root] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop
  + [method_source] is periphery_focus
  + [primitive_flow] is periphery signal to focus draw to analysis to delineation to relation tracing to sparse realization to dense node
  + [sparse_realization] is an early insight, relation, suspicion, contrast, or boundary pressure preserved before it is stable enough to become authority
  + [dense_node] is a scoped subject record that has survived delineation, inside/outside scoping, relation typing, and evidence support
  + [causal_relationship] is a supported cause, dependency, mechanism, or enabling condition
  + [casual_relationship] is a loose, nearby, opportunistic, resembling, social, coincidental, or low-pressure association that may guide attention but does not prove cause
  + [scope_out_and_in] is first exclude what the subject is not, then admit what belongs after boundary testing
  + [authority_boundary] is source direction only until processed into a project-local framework contract
  + [inside] is periphery inspection, focus draw, delineation, relation typing, sparse realization records, dense node records, and scoped in/out boundaries
  + [outside] is proof by association, automatic densification, treating casual relation as causal relation, and forcing early realizations into authority

  = must: preserve sparse realizations without inflating them into dense nodes too early
  = must: distinguish causal relationships from casual relationships
  = must: require delineation before a dense node is accepted
  = must: scope subjects out and in before authority is assigned
  = must: use this framework by applying it to active RiemannHypothesis periphery
  - never: let a compelling realization bypass boundary testing
